🔁 The Loop You’re Describing

At its core, it’s this cycle:

Pattern → Test → Feedback → Update → Repeat

* Pattern → your current model (“this is how I think things work”)
* Test → action, experiment, or even just observation
* Feedback → what actually happened
* Update → adjust the model
* Repeat → iterate and refine

That loop is everywhere:

* science experiments
* athletes improving form
* entrepreneurs testing ideas
* even conversations and social skills

⸻

🧠 Why this is so powerful

Because reality acts like a filter:

* Bad patterns → break under testing
* Good patterns → survive and strengthen

Over time, you’re not just guessing—you’re converging toward what actually works

